The evidence with the title 'Ten years of the bush tax cuts benefiting the rich ' says On june 7, 2001, president George W. Bush signed into law the Economic Growth And Tax Relief Reconciliation Act , the first of two "Bush tax cuts.  ... The bottom 20 percent ( making less than $ 20,000 ) received only a 1 percent share of the Bush tax cuts; 75 percent of these low-income families saw no tax benefit at all . 
